<dl id="n40043a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40043a">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40043a"> 43(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> tempter</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In the book of Job he presents himself before the Lord among the sons of God (ii. 1), yet he is represented both as accuser and tempter. He disbelieves in Job&apos;s integrity, and desires him to be so tried that he may fall into sin. <small> &ldquo;DEVIL&rdquo; <a name="EBDV" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBDV"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) VIII 122</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
